        "teachingPoint": "In a live disruption, the quality of your Block 1 input is what drives the response plan's usefulness. Be specific: name the disruption type (supplier insolvency, force majeure, logistics failure, quality recall), the affected volumes and time horizon, and your current inventory cover in days. The more operational detail you provide, the more immediately actionable the containment and continuity recommendations will be.",
