        "teachingPoint": "The most differentiated input you can provide is your supplier concentration data: what percentage of your category spend is with your top 3 suppliers? This single data point drives the supply concentration risk score more than any other variable. If you do not have exact figures, provide an estimate — EXOS will apply a conservative default and flag the assumption. Geographic sourcing data (country of origin) is the second most important input.",
        "hook": "Category risk profiles based on last year's data miss the risks developing right now. EXOS evaluates your supply category across four risk dimensions — concentration, geographic exposure, regulatory change, and demand volatility — and enriches your internal data with real-time market intelligence. Your risk profile reflects today's supply market, not an 18-month-old snapshot.",
