        "teachingPoint": "The most valuable input for Black Swan analysis is your critical dependency mapping in Block 2 — identify the single points of failure that would stop your operations: which suppliers have no approved alternative, which geographic routes have no backup, which regulatory approvals cannot be transferred to another supplier. These are the nodes where Black Swan scenarios have the highest impact concentration.",
        "hook": "Black Swan events are rarely completely unpredictable — they have precursor signals that risk teams didn't take seriously. EXOS identifies current precursor signals in your specific supply chain using real-time market intelligence, then models extreme-risk scenarios and pre-emptive resilience strategies. Build your resilience before it becomes urgent — not after a crisis has already started.",
        "persona": "Project Procurement Manager"
