        "description": "SITUATION: A Component Procurement Manager suspects significant value leakage is hiding in the tail of the semiconductors and PCB assemblies spend portfolio — fragmented suppliers, off-contract purchasing, and unclassified POs that never made it into the category strategy. The raw data exists in the ERP, but it's a wall of unstructured text that nobody has had the time to clean and classify properly.\n\nHOW TO USE EXOS: Select S5 — Spend Analytics. In Block 1, describe your industry and the scope of spend data you are analysing. In Block 2, upload or paste your spend export — the minimum required columns are supplier name (anonymised to Supplier_001 format per GDPR requirements), spend amount, transaction date, and a free-text description of what was purchased. A minimum of 5 line items is required; the analysis becomes statistically meaningful at 50+ lines. In Block 3, provide any existing category mapping you have (even partial), your preferred taxonomy standard (UNSPSC or custom), and any known maverick or off-contract supplier flags.\n\nWHAT YOU RECEIVE: A fully classified spend taxonomy with AI confidence scoring on each line item — low-confidence classifications are flagged for human review rather than silently misclassified. You receive a supplier consolidation opportunity list ranked by annual savings potential, a maverick spend heat map showing off-contract purchasing by category and department, and a tail spend analysis displaying the 80/20 distribution of your supplier base.\n\nWHY IT MATTERS: Gartner benchmarks show that organisations with mature spend analytics achieve 6–10% annual cost reduction compared to those without. The savings are not in the strategic categories you already manage well — they are in the tail. Manual classification in Excel misses cross-supplier patterns that only become visible at scale. EXOS processes hundreds of line items in seconds, with category-specific intelligence that generic spreadsheet tools simply cannot replicate.",
