        "title": "Supply market risk profile for electronic components and contract manufacturing",
        "ref": "S20 — Category Risk Evaluation",
        "feature": "Category Risk Evaluation (S20)",
        "description": "SITUATION: A Procurement Manager is reviewing the sourcing strategy for electronic components and contract manufacturing and needs to understand the current risk profile of the supply market — not just internal risks, but external dynamics: how concentrated is the supplier market, what geopolitical or regulatory events could affect supply continuity, and what early warning signals should the team be monitoring?\n\nHOW TO USE EXOS: Select S20 — Category Risk Evaluation. In Block 1, describe your industry and the category in detail: include the supply chain geography, the strategic importance of the category to your operations, and any historical disruption events you have experienced. In Block 2, provide your category baseline data: number of active suppliers and the approximate spend concentration with your top 3, annual category spend, key supply chain geography (sourcing country/region), and whether any materials or services in the category are subject to regulatory restriction or emissions obligations. In Block 3, add strategic risk factors: known geopolitical exposure, demand volatility driven by your own business pipeline, and any regulatory changes in your sector that could affect supply requirements.\n\nWHAT YOU RECEIVE: A multi-dimensional category risk profile with scored risk assessments across four dimensions — supply concentration, geographic exposure, regulatory change exposure, and demand volatility. You receive a supplier concentration analysis showing your dependency risk and diversification options, specific mitigation recommendations prioritised by risk severity, and an early-warning signal assessment based on current real-time market intelligence from EXOS's Perplexity grounding layer.\n\nWHY IT MATTERS: Category risk evaluations based on last year's data miss the risks that are developing right now. Supply market concentration in critical categories has accelerated significantly across European industry since 2020 — sectors that appeared well-diversified in pre-pandemic risk assessments proved highly fragile when tested. EXOS enriches your internal data with live market intelligence, ensuring your risk profile reflects current market reality — not a static snapshot that was accurate 18 months ago.",
        "teachingPoint": "The most differentiated input you can provide is your supplier concentration data: what percentage of your category spend is with your top 3 suppliers? This single data point drives the supply concentration risk score more than any other variable. If you do not have exact figures, provide an estimate — EXOS will apply a conservative default and flag the assumption. Geographic sourcing data (country of origin) is the second most important input.",
        "hook": "Category risk profiles based on last year's data miss the risks developing right now. EXOS evaluates your supply category across four risk dimensions — concentration, geographic exposure, regulatory change, and demand volatility — and enriches your internal data with real-time market intelligence. Your risk profile reflects today's supply market, not an 18-month-old snapshot.",
