        "description": "SITUATION: A Supply Chain Lead receives a supplier-drafted contract for a significant heavy equipment and explosives procurement and needs to identify the key risks before it goes to legal review. The document is 40 pages of dense commercial terms. Legal review costs €250–500 per hour. The procurement team needs to understand the commercial risk landscape before deciding which clauses to escalate — and ideally, they need that view today.\n\nHOW TO USE EXOS: Select S13 — Contract Analysis. In Block 1, describe your industry, the category and the strategic importance of this contract — is this a critical supplier, a new relationship, or a renewal? In Block 2, paste the full contract text or the key commercial sections: scope of work, pricing and payment terms, SLAs and remedies, liability and indemnification clauses, termination provisions, and any auto-renewal or price escalation mechanisms. If the contract is long, prioritise the commercial, liability, and termination sections — these contain 80% of the financial risk. In Block 3, provide context: your organisation's standard risk appetite (e.g. liability caps, acceptable IP assignment terms), any regulatory requirements that must be reflected, and the commercial importance of this supplier.\n\nWHAT YOU RECEIVE: A structured contract risk analysis flagging: liability exposure (uncapped, asymmetric, or disproportionate clauses), auto-renewal traps and notice period requirements, missing or weak SLA definitions, intellectual property assignment risks, termination for convenience restrictions that limit your exit options, and price escalation mechanisms that create future cost uncertainty. The output includes a prioritised redline recommendation list — sorted by financial impact — so legal knows exactly where to focus its review time.\n\nWHY IT MATTERS: The most expensive contract risks are the ones nobody reads until they materialise. Auto-renewal clauses lock organisations into unwanted contracts; uncapped liability clauses create existential exposure; missing SLA remedies leave performance failures without financial consequence. EXOS does not replace legal review — it makes legal review dramatically more efficient by doing the first-pass risk triage in minutes, so your lawyers focus their €400/hour expertise on the genuine complexities rather than the mechanical read-through.",
