        "title": "Contract risk review and redline brief for drilling equipment and well services",
        "ref": "S13 — Contract Analysis",
        "feature": "Contract Analyser",
        "description": "SITUATION: A Supply Chain Manager receives a supplier-drafted contract for a significant drilling equipment and well services procurement and needs to identify the key risks before it goes to legal review. The document is 40 pages of dense commercial terms. Legal review costs €250–500 per hour. The procurement team needs to understand the commercial risk landscape before deciding which clauses to escalate — and ideally, they need that view today.\n\nHOW TO USE EXOS: Select S13 — Contract Analysis. In Block 1, describe your industry, the category and the strategic importance of this contract — is this a critical supplier, a new relationship, or a renewal? In Block 2, paste the full contract text or the key commercial sections: scope of work, pricing and payment terms, SLAs and remedies, liability and indemnification clauses, termination provisions, and any auto-renewal or price escalation mechanisms. If the contract is long, prioritise the commercial, liability, and termination sections — these contain 80% of the financial risk. In Block 3, provide context: your organisation's standard risk appetite (e.g. liability caps, acceptable IP assignment terms), any regulatory requirements that must be reflected, and the commercial importance of this supplier.\n\nWHAT YOU RECEIVE: A structured contract risk analysis flagging: liability exposure (uncapped, asymmetric, or disproportionate clauses), auto-renewal traps and notice period requirements, missing or weak SLA definitions, intellectual property assignment risks, termination for convenience restrictions that limit your exit options, and price escalation mechanisms that create future cost uncertainty. The output includes a prioritised redline recommendation list — sorted by financial impact — so legal knows exactly where to focus its review time.\n\nWHY IT MATTERS: The most expensive contract risks are the ones nobody reads until they materialise. Auto-renewal clauses lock organisations into unwanted contracts; uncapped liability clauses create existential exposure; missing SLA remedies leave performance failures without financial consequence. EXOS does not replace legal review — it makes legal review dramatically more efficient by doing the first-pass risk triage in minutes, so your lawyers focus their €400/hour expertise on the genuine complexities rather than the mechanical read-through.",
        "teachingPoint": "Focus your Block 2 input on the commercial and legal sections with the highest financial risk: pricing and payment terms, SLA and remedy provisions, liability and indemnification, termination rights, and any escalation or benchmarking mechanisms. If pasting a full contract, EXOS will process it — but if you have limited time, the liability, termination, and auto-renewal sections are always the highest priority for first-pass review.",
        "hook": "Auto-renewal clauses, uncapped liability, and missing SLA remedies hide in contracts until they cost you money. EXOS performs a first-pass contract risk analysis in minutes — flagging the top commercial risks and producing a prioritised redline brief so your legal team focuses on the clauses that matter, not the pages that don't.",
