        "title": "EU-compliant RFP for SaaS licences and cloud services competitive tender",
        "ref": "S9 — RFP Generator",
        "feature": "RFP Generator",
        "description": "SITUATION: A IT Procurement Manager needs to launch a competitive tender for SaaS licences and cloud services and is staring at a blank document. Writing a well-structured RFP from scratch — with clear scope definitions, evaluation criteria, SLA schedules, and compliance requirements — typically takes days of drafting and multiple rounds of stakeholder review. The category is time-sensitive and the blank page is the bottleneck.\n\nHOW TO USE EXOS: Select S9 — RFP Generator. In Block 1, describe your industry, organisation size, and the category: what you are buying, what business problem it solves, and the regulatory or compliance context that applies. In Block 2, define the core requirements: the asset or service specification, contract duration, estimated annual value or volume, key performance indicators you expect the supplier to meet, and any mandatory qualifications or certifications (ISO standards, EU compliance frameworks, sector-specific accreditations). In Block 3, add the commercial and governance parameters: payment terms, liquidated damages expectations, reporting requirements, transition provisions, and any known supplier market dynamics that should shape the evaluation approach.\n\nWHAT YOU RECEIVE: A fully structured, EU-compliant RFP document including: an executive summary of the requirement, a detailed scope of work, mandatory and desirable requirements listed separately, a weighted evaluation scorecard with criteria and scoring methodology, SLA schedules with KPI definitions and remedies, commercial terms and conditions, and a supplier response template. The output is formatted for immediate use — not a rough outline but a document you can issue to suppliers.\n\nWHY IT MATTERS: RFP quality directly determines competition quality. Vague, incomplete RFPs produce vague, incomparable supplier responses — forcing procurement to run clarification rounds that extend timelines by weeks. Industry benchmarks show that well-structured RFPs produce 12–18% more competitive pricing responses than poorly specified tenders, simply because suppliers can price with confidence rather than adding risk buffers. EXOS generates the structural scaffolding of a professional RFP in minutes, so your team spends its time on strategy and stakeholder alignment — not document formatting.",
        "teachingPoint": "The quality of your RFP output is directly determined by Block 2 — your requirements definition. Be specific about KPIs and performance standards you expect: 'on-time delivery' is not a KPI, but '98.5% on-time delivery measured monthly with a €500/day liquidated damage remedy' is. EXOS will structure whatever level of detail you provide, but the more precise your requirements, the more supplier-ready the output.",
        "hook": "Poorly specified RFPs produce bids that cannot be compared — forcing clarification rounds that extend procurement timelines by weeks and give suppliers room to hide cost. EXOS generates a fully structured, EU-compliant RFP in minutes. Industry benchmarks show well-structured tenders produce 12–18% more competitive pricing responses, simply because suppliers can price with confidence.",
